# clang-format policy for everything under src/.
#
# src/aarch64/ (and the shared-root imports) hold VIXL-derived sources whose
# byte-identity against upstream is a spec invariant (see
# specs/aarch64-simulator/spec.md and design.md decision D5). `DisableFormat:
# true` keeps clang-format from touching them — even small formatter-version
# differences (e.g. spacing around binary operators in template expressions)
# would silently introduce drift not bracketed by `// gaby-vm:` markers.
#
# `BasedOnStyle: InheritParentConfig` makes this config build on the root
# `.clang-format` instead of the LLVM default. For imported sources that is
# inert — `DisableFormat: true` means the base style is never applied. It
# matters for src/gaby_vm/: that directory holds project-authored code and has
# its own `.clang-format` that re-enables formatting. `InheritParentConfig`
# only climbs past this file to the root Google config when this file opts in
# too; without this line, code under src/gaby_vm/ would be formatted
# LLVM-style instead of matching the rest of the project.

BasedOnStyle: InheritParentConfig
DisableFormat: true
SortIncludes: Never
